<item>
            <title>[SPARK-24143] filter empty blocks when convert mapstatus to (blockId, size) pair</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-24143</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In current code(MapOutputTracker.convertMapStatuses), mapstatus are converted to (blockId, size) pair for all blocks &amp;#8211; no matter the block is empty or not, which result in OOM when there are lots of consecutive empty blocks, especially when adaptive execution is enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(blockId, size) pair is only used in ShuffleBlockFetcherIterator to control shuffle-read and only non-empty block request is sent. Can we just filter out the empty blocks in  MapOutputTracker.convertMapStatuses and save memory?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
